OL,3,CSeaside big wheel under threat
OL,5,FMellors wants to put up its 45-metre
OL,6,Fwheel, a ticket office and a catering
OL,7,Funit in the council-owned Princess
OL,8,FGardens.
OL,10,FIt would pay #30,000 towards
OL,11,Fresurfacing pathways.
OL,13,FIn response, a council spokesman said:
OL,14,F"In this case, officers have concluded
OL,15,Fthat the harm to local heritage
OL,16,Foutweighs the benefits presented."
OL,18,FThe Torbay Heritage Trust has
OL,19,Fcomplained that the permission is 'not
OL,20,Ftruly temporary' as the wheel comes
OL,21,Fback every summer.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/7
