OL,3,CSeaside big wheel under threat
OL,5,F"As well as causing physical damage to
OL,6,Fthe park and garden, the proposed
OL,7,Fdevelopment would block views and
OL,8,Fdominate the space, thereby removing
OL,9,Fthe sense of tranquillity of the
OL,10,Fgardens."
OL,12,FA council spokesperson added:
OL,13,F"Officers found that the principle of
OL,14,Fthe temporary provision of an
OL,15,Fobservation wheel and ancillary
OL,16,Fdevelopment is considered to align
OL,17,Fwith the development plan aspirations
OL,18,Fin terms of supporting and promoting
OL,19,Ftourism facilities and the management
OL,20,Fof local green spaces.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/7
